The Best Rainbow

I saw the best rainbow last Tuesday. It was after school, and the rain had stopped.

The sky was still grey, like an old blanket. But there it wasâ€”a huge rainbow over the park.

It was not faint or wobbly. It was bright and strong. I could see all the colours: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and purple. The purple was hard to spot, but I found it.

The rainbow seemed to touch the ground near the swings. I ran towards it, but it moved away. Mum says you can never reach the end. I think she is right.

What I liked most was how it made everyone stop and look. A man with a dog. A girl on a bike. Even Mrs Patel from the corner shop. We all stood there, wet and smiling.

Then the sun went in, and the rainbow faded. But I still remember it.

That is my favourite kind of rainbow. The sort that makes strangers friends, just for a moment. [end of text]


